        },
        {
          "id": "bfc90fd241fa_11",
          "href": null,
          "name": "bfbf",
          "text": "One of Lovelock’s close collaborators in the development of Gaia theory was the biologist Lynn Margulis. Dorian Sagan and Lynn Margulis argue: “Clearly life on the planet is some kind of interacting unity” and suggest “if symbiosis is defined as the living together in protracted physical continuity of different kinds of organisms then … Gaia is simply symbiosis seen from space” (Sagan & Margulis, 1993, p.353). Lovelock has described Gaia theory as planetary physiology or as “a practical science of planetary medicine” (Lovelock, 2000).",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
