        {
          "id": "bfc90fd241fa_13",
          "href": null,
          "name": "5f60",
          "text": "In Gaia — The human journey from chaos to cosmos, Elisabet Sahtouris suggests: “Living and non-living matter are continuous, such that life is no more, no less than a geological process that becomes a biogeochemical process through its own transformation over time.” (1989, p.57). Sahtouris has since dared to go a step further and has suggested that by a similar argument it may not be useful to make such a either-or distinction between living and dead matter. It may, in fact, be useful to explore a perspective that regards the entire universe as a continuous evolutionary living process. In Prologue to a New Model of the Living Universe she writes:",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 68,
              "href": "http://www.sahtouris.com/",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 50,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 642,
              "href": "http://www.sahtouris.com/pdfs/MindBeforeMatterChapter.pdf",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 596,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 48,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 3,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "bfc90fd241fa_14",
          "href": null,
          "name": "e3de",
          "text": "“Instead of projecting a universe of mechanism without inventor, assembling blindly through particular, atomic and molecular collisions a few of which came magically to life and further evolved by accidental mutations, I propose that there is reason to see the whole universe as alive, self-organizing endless fractal levels of living complexity as reflexive systems learning to play with possibilities in the intelligent co-creation of complex evolving systems. I propose that it is actually more reasonable to project our life onto the entire universe than our non-living machinery, which is a derivative of life, a truly emerging phenomenon, rather than a fundamental one. I propose that it is possible to create a scientific model of a living universe, and that such a model is not only scientifically justified but can lead to the wisdom required to build a better human life on and for our planet Earth … Toward that end, I propose:",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 938,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "PQ"
        },
        {
          "id": "bfc90fd241fa_15",
          "href": null,
          "name": "4c1d",
          "text": "The scientific definition of reality should be the collective human experience of self, world and universe as inner and outer worlds perceived from individually unique perspectives. (We have no other legitimate basis for creating cosmic models.)",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 245,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "PQ"
        },
        {
          "id": "bfc90fd241fa_16",
          "href": null,
          "name": "3896",
          "text": "Consciousness (awareness) shall be axiomatic for the simple and obvious reason that no human experience can happen outside it.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
